The fireball was captured on camera on Sunday by the United Kingdom Meteor Observing Network (UKMON) in Portadown, County Armagh .
Footage shows it glowing brightly as it races northwards towards the Irish Sea .
It comes after astronomers revealed that a meteor that streaked across the sky above Chelyabinsk in Russia in 2013 triggered the conversion of biblical figure Paul, one of the most influential figures in early Christianity .